</span>
</span></p><p>A few years back, when I saw a fresh artichoke at the farmers market for the first time, I knew immediately that I&#8217;d be taking it home. It was so pretty, with its tightly packed petals and thick stem tinged with purple. How could I resist it? But when I got back to the house, I realized that I had one <em>tiny </em>problem&#8230;.I had no clue how to cook artichokes.</p><p>That spring, I passed off the artichoke prep to my mom, who happened to be visiting (thanks, Mom!), but since then, I&#8217;ve mastered how to cook artichokes myself. I wanted to share my method today because it&#8217;s peak artichoke season, and fresh artichokes are just too good to miss out on. The leaves are meaty and satisfying, with a nutty flavor that&#8217;s bright with lemon. Serve them with a tasty dipping sauce or melted butter for a fresh spring appetizer that simply can&#8217;t be beat.</p><p>
<span
class="pibfi_pinterest ">
<img
class="alignnone wp-image-56347 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0naHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmcnIHdpZHRoPScxMTYwJyBoZWlnaHQ9JzEzMDUnPjwvc3ZnPg==" data-original=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/artichoke-heart-recipe.jpg alt="Hands peeling off small, tough petals" width=1160 height=1305 data-pin-description="Learn how to cook artichokes perfectly every time! This simple steamed artichokes recipe is a delicious, healthy spring appetizer. Serve the tender leaves with a tasty sauce or melted butter for dipping! | Love and Lemons #artichoke #spring #appetizers #healthy" data-srcset="https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/artichoke-heart-recipe.jpg 1160w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/artichoke-heart-recipe-267x300.jpg 267w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/artichoke-heart-recipe-910x1024.jpg 910w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/artichoke-heart-recipe-89x100.jpg 89w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/artichoke-heart-recipe-580x653.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1160px) 100vw, 1160px" data-pin-url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/ >
<span
class=xc_pin onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/&media=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/artichoke-heart-recipe.jpg&description=Learn+how+to+cook+artichokes+perfectly+every+time%21+This+simple+steamed+artichokes+recipe+is+a+delicious%2C+healthy+spring+appetizer.+Serve+the+tender+leaves+with+a+tasty+sauce+or+melted+butter+for+dipping%21+%7C+Love+and+Lemons+%23artichoke+%23spring+%23appetizers+%23healthy')">
</span>
</span></p><h2>How to Prepare An Artichoke</h2><p>Preparing artichokes for the first time can be daunting, but don&#8217;t let it intimidate you! Once you learn how, it&#8217;s a breeze. Here&#8217;s what you need to do:</p><p><strong>First, make sure you have the right equipment. </strong>Artichokes start to brown as soon as you cut them. To reduce this oxidation, you&#8217;ll need a quartered lemon to rub on the cut surfaces of the artichoke. I also recommend using a stainless steel knife instead of a carbon-steel one, which can increase browning. In addition, you&#8217;ll need a cutting board, a peeler, a large pot, and a steamer basket.</p><p><strong>Start by preparing the stem. </strong>Peel off any tough, small petals on the artichoke stem.</p><p>
<span
class="pibfi_pinterest ">
<img
class="alignnone wp-image-56358 size-full" src=data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0naHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmcnIHdpZHRoPScxMTYwJyBoZWlnaHQ9JzgzMSc+PC9zdmc+ data-original=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/what-is-artichoke.jpg alt="Hands trimming stem with knife" width=1160 height=831 data-pin-description="Learn how to cook artichokes perfectly every time! This simple steamed artichokes recipe is a delicious, healthy spring appetizer. Serve the tender leaves with a tasty sauce or melted butter for dipping! | Love and Lemons #artichoke #spring #appetizers #healthy" data-srcset="https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/what-is-artichoke.jpg 1160w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/what-is-artichoke-300x215.jpg 300w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/what-is-artichoke-1024x734.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/what-is-artichoke-100x72.jpg 100w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/what-is-artichoke-580x416.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1160px) 100vw, 1160px" data-pin-url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/ >
<span
class=xc_pin onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/&media=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/what-is-artichoke.jpg&description=Learn+how+to+cook+artichokes+perfectly+every+time%21+This+simple+steamed+artichokes+recipe+is+a+delicious%2C+healthy+spring+appetizer.+Serve+the+tender+leaves+with+a+tasty+sauce+or+melted+butter+for+dipping%21+%7C+Love+and+Lemons+%23artichoke+%23spring+%23appetizers+%23healthy')">
</span>
</span></p><p>Then, use your knife to trim the end of the stem. You only need to cut off a little bit! The stem is completely edible, and it has a wonderful meaty texture. You&#8217;ll definitely want to cook and eat it.</p><p>
<span
class="pibfi_pinterest ">
<img
class="alignnone wp-image-56351 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0naHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmcnIHdpZHRoPScxMTYwJyBoZWlnaHQ9JzEyMTMnPjwvc3ZnPg==" data-original=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-long-to-steam-artichokes.jpg alt="Hands scoring artichoke stem with knife" width=1160 height=1213 data-pin-description="Learn how to cook artichokes perfectly every time! This simple steamed artichokes recipe is a delicious, healthy spring appetizer. Serve the tender leaves with a tasty sauce or melted butter for dipping! | Love and Lemons #artichoke #spring #appetizers #healthy" data-srcset="https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-long-to-steam-artichokes.jpg 1160w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-long-to-steam-artichokes-287x300.jpg 287w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-long-to-steam-artichokes-979x1024.jpg 979w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-long-to-steam-artichokes-96x100.jpg 96w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-long-to-steam-artichokes-580x607.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1160px) 100vw, 1160px" data-pin-url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/ >
<span
class=xc_pin onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/&media=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-long-to-steam-artichokes.jpg&description=Learn+how+to+cook+artichokes+perfectly+every+time%21+This+simple+steamed+artichokes+recipe+is+a+delicious%2C+healthy+spring+appetizer.+Serve+the+tender+leaves+with+a+tasty+sauce+or+melted+butter+for+dipping%21+%7C+Love+and+Lemons+%23artichoke+%23spring+%23appetizers+%23healthy')">
</span>
</span></p><p>After you trim the stem, gently score it to help it cook more quickly. Now&#8217;s the time to use that lemon! Rub it over the stem&#8217;s cut surface to prevent browning.</p><p>
<span
class="pibfi_pinterest ">
<img
class="alignnone wp-image-56356 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0naHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmcnIHdpZHRoPScxMTYwJyBoZWlnaHQ9JzEwMjknPjwvc3ZnPg==" data-original=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-steam-artichokes.jpg alt="How to cook artichokes - peeling tough outer stem" width=1160 height=1029 data-pin-description="Learn how to cook artichokes perfectly every time! This simple steamed artichokes recipe is a delicious, healthy spring appetizer. Serve the tender leaves with a tasty sauce or melted butter for dipping! | Love and Lemons #artichoke #spring #appetizers #healthy" data-srcset="https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-steam-artichokes.jpg 1160w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-steam-artichokes-300x266.jpg 300w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-steam-artichokes-1024x908.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-steam-artichokes-100x89.jpg 100w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-steam-artichokes-580x515.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1160px) 100vw, 1160px" data-pin-url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/ >
<span
class=xc_pin onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/&media=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-steam-artichokes.jpg&description=Learn+how+to+cook+artichokes+perfectly+every+time%21+This+simple+steamed+artichokes+recipe+is+a+delicious%2C+healthy+spring+appetizer.+Serve+the+tender+leaves+with+a+tasty+sauce+or+melted+butter+for+dipping%21+%7C+Love+and+Lemons+%23artichoke+%23spring+%23appetizers+%23healthy')">
</span>
</span></p><p>Next, grab your peeler. Use it to trim away the tough outer skin of the artichoke stem. Then, rub the peeled sides of the stem with lemon juice.</p><p>
<span
class="pibfi_pinterest ">
<img
class="alignnone wp-image-56353 size-full" src=data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0naHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmcnIHdpZHRoPScxMTYwJyBoZWlnaHQ9Jzk5NCc+PC9zdmc+ data-original=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-eat-artichoke.jpg alt="How to prepare an artichoke - slicing off top with knife" width=1160 height=994 data-pin-description="Learn how to cook artichokes perfectly every time! This simple steamed artichokes recipe is a delicious, healthy spring appetizer. Serve the tender leaves with a tasty sauce or melted butter for dipping! | Love and Lemons #artichoke #spring #appetizers #healthy" data-srcset="https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-eat-artichoke.jpg 1160w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-eat-artichoke-300x257.jpg 300w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-eat-artichoke-1024x877.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-eat-artichoke-100x86.jpg 100w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-eat-artichoke-580x497.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1160px) 100vw, 1160px" data-pin-url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/ >
<span
class=xc_pin onclick="pin_this(event, 'http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/&media=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-eat-artichoke.jpg&description=Learn+how+to+cook+artichokes+perfectly+every+time%21+This+simple+steamed+artichokes+recipe+is+a+delicious%2C+healthy+spring+appetizer.+Serve+the+tender+leaves+with+a+tasty+sauce+or+melted+butter+for+dipping%21+%7C+Love+and+Lemons+%23artichoke+%23spring+%23appetizers+%23healthy')">
</span>
</span></p><p><strong>Next, prepare the artichoke leaves. </strong>Slice 1/2-1 inch off the top of the artichoke.</p><p>
<span
class="pibfi_pinterest ">
<img
class="alignnone wp-image-56354 size-full" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0naHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmcnIHdpZHRoPScxMTYwJyBoZWlnaHQ9JzEwNTInPjwvc3ZnPg==" data-original=https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-make-artichokes.jpg alt="Trimmed artichoke on a cutting board" width=1160 height=1052 data-pin-description="Learn how to cook artichokes perfectly every time! This simple steamed artichokes recipe is a delicious, healthy spring appetizer. Serve the tender leaves with a tasty sauce or melted butter for dipping! | Love and Lemons #artichoke #spring #appetizers #healthy" data-srcset="https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-make-artichokes.jpg 1160w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-make-artichokes-300x272.jpg 300w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-make-artichokes-1024x929.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-make-artichokes-100x91.jpg 100w, https://cdn.loveandlemons.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/how-to-make-artichokes-580x526.jpg 580w" sizes="(max-width: 1160px) 100vw, 1160px" data-pin-url=https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-cook-artichokes/ >
<span
