</span>
</span></p><p>Unless you&#8217;re working with baby artichokes, there&#8217;s one more step before you eat! You need to remove the choke (in baby artichokes, the choke is edible). To do this, slice the steamed artichoke in half lengthwise. Use a small spoon to scoop out the hairy choke, which sits between the cup-shaped artichoke heart and the tender inner leaves.</p><p>Note: The choke has not been scooped out of the artichokes in the photo below. It&#8217;s the fuzzy section right under the small, purple-tipped leaves.</p><p>
